data.name: GYM: 5 DAY PPL Upper/Lower
data.description: The PPL Upper/Lower is Mike’s favourite split of 2025. It combines the infamous PPL split with an added upper and lower day allowing for all muscle groups to be trained twice per week. This is for intermediate - advanced lifters who are focused on building strength, size and hitting all muscle groups equally. A great opportunity to increase weights lifted and hit PR’s with the reduced rep ranges and increased rest periods. *This is only available as a 5 day option. Focus muscle groups - full body Day 1 - Push 4 Day 2 - Pull 4 Day 3 - Legs 4 Day 4 - Rest (LISS) Day 5 - Upper 2 Day 6 - Lower 4 Day 7 - Rest (Core, LISS)  Day 1 - Push 4 A: Hammer Plate Press (Flat) B: Smith Machine Shoulder Press C: Flat or Incline DB Fly D: Machine Lateral Raise E: Tricep Dip Machine F: Single Arm Cable Tricep Extension G: Overhead Tricep Extension Machine  Day 2 - Pull 4 A: Seated One Arm Iso Row (Neutral) B: Lat Pulldown (Underhand Grip) C: Low Row D: Incline Bench DB Rear Delt Fly E: Single Arm DB Hammer Curl F: BB/EZ Bar Bicep Curl G: Bicep Focus Chin Up  Day 3 - Legs 4 A: Romanian Deadlift (Glute Focus) B: Hack Squat C: Seated Leg Curl D: Leg Extension E: Lying Leg Curl (Single Leg) F: Standing Calf Raise  Day 4 - Rest  Day 5 - Upper C A: T-Bar Row B: Incline BB Bench Press C: Iso Lateral High Row D: Chest Supported DB Lateral Raise E: DY DB Shrugs F: Cable Rear Delt Fly (Single Arm) G: Machine Preacher Curl H: Close Grip BB Press (Smith Machine)  Day 6 - Lower 4 A: Smith Machine Hip Thrust B: Pendulum Squat C: Smith Machine Bulgarian Split Squat D: Weighted 45’s E: Leg Press (Quad Focus) F: Leg Press Calf Raise  Day 7 - Rest (Core, LISS)
